-- Odebrecht Wins $500 Million Contract for Lima Road Project
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2012-09-19T16:13:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-19/odebrecht-wins-500-million-contract-for-lima-road-project.html
Odebrecht SA won a $500 million
contract to improve a network of highways in and around the
Peruvian capital  Lima .  The  Salvador , Brazil-based company will improve 115
kilometers (72 miles) of the Pan-American and central Andean
highways, and build 36 interchanges as well as pedestrian
crossings and pavements, the city said in a statement on its
 website . Work will start next year and terminate in 2015, it
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
